I"	<ol>
  <li>Melt butter in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and spinach. Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes or until spinach has wilted. Stir in cream. Simmer for 2 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.</li>
  <li>Add stock and 2 cups cold water to saucepan. Cover. Bring to the boil over high heat. Add polenta. Reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 to 7 minutes or until polenta is thick.</li>
  <li>Return spinach mixture to pan. Add cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Serve.</li>
</ol>
